text: The Palawan bubble-nest frog (Philautus longicrus) is a frog. It lives in the Phillippines, Indonesia, Borneo, and Malaysia. In the Phillippines, people have seen it between 30 and 1000 meters above sea level, and in Borneo, people have seen it between 700 and 2900 meters above sea level. ==Paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Philautus longicrus
